{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775837184178,"sessionID":"ses_287ddf2ddffeKgyYIqXjT8EJwx","part":{"id":"prt_d7824fc5b001095rCBipkYB3dO","messageID":"msg_d7824f0620017jWk1nS11Z7NyU","sessionID":"ses_287ddf2ddffeKgyYIqXjT8EJwx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_c763599af8e44fb0ae8fada4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** pkg/store\n4: > **Language:** Go\n5: > **Size:** S\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-014/design.md`, `changes/AR-014/proposal.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n8: \n9: ## T1. 实现 Valkey 构造函数\n10: \n11: - [ ] 1.1 创建 `store_valkey.go`，定义 `valkeyStore` 结构体（`cli valkey.Client`, `sessionPrefix`, `expiryIndexKey`, `lastActivityIndexKey`）\n12: - [ ] 1.2 实现 `newValkeyStore() (Store, error)` 构造函数\n13: - [ ] 1.3 验证 `VALKEY_ADDR` 非空，否则返回 `errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")`\n14: - [ ] 1.4 验证 `VALKEY_PASSWORD`（除非 `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`）\n15: - [ ] 1.5 支持 `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` 和 `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` 环境变量\n16: - [ ] 1.6 使用 `valkey.NewClient` 创建客户端（不执行 ping，连接惰性验证）\n17: - [ ] 1.7 更新 `singleton.go` 中 `initStore()` 支持 `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n18: - [ ] 1.8 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingAddr`\n19: - [ ] 1.9 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingPassword`\n20: - [ ] 1.10 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordNotRequired`\n21: - [ ] 1.11 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordRequiredTrue`\n22: \n23: **Verification:** `newValkeyStore` 签名返回 `(Store, error)`；无 `klog.Fatal` 调用；singleton.go 正确处理 error；构造测试全绿\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## T2. 实现 Valkey CRUD 操作\n28: \n29: - [ ] 2.1 实现 `sessionKey(sessionID string) string` 辅助方法（返回 `v.sessionPrefix + sessionID`）\n30: - [ ] 2.2 实现 `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` — `B().Ping().Build()` 校验 `\"PONG\"`\n31: - [ ] 2.3 实现 `GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` — `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`，`valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → `ErrNotFound`\n32: - [ ] 2.4 实现 `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID, info)` — 验证 nil/零 ExpiresAt，`DoMulti`: SETNX + ZADD expiry + ZADD activity\n33: - [ ] 2.5 实现 `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID, info)` — `B().Set().Key().Value().Xx().Build()`，响应非 `\"OK\"` 返回 `\"key not exists\"` 错误\n34: - [ ] 2.6 实现 `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` — `DoMulti`: DEL + ZREM expiry + ZREM activity\n35: - [ ] 2.7 实现 `Close() error` — 调用 `v.cli.Close()`\n36: - [ ] 2.8 运行 `go build ./pkg/store/...` 确认编译通过\n37: \n38: **Verification:** 所有方法签名与 `Store` 接口一致（design.md §3.1）；`go build` 零错误\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## T3. 实现 Valkey 查询操作\n43: \n44: - [ ] 3.1 实现 `ListSandboxes(ctx)` — `ZRANGE` 0 -1 + 逐个 `GetSandbox`，跳过 `ErrNotFound`（孤儿 ZSET 成员容错），返回 `map[string]*types.SandboxInfo`\n45: - [ ] 3.2 实现 `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` — `limit <= 0` 返回 `nil, nil`；`ZRANGEBYSCORE` `-inf` 到 `before.Unix()` + 逐个 `GetSandbox`\n46: - [ ] 3.3 实现 `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` — 同 3.2，目标 key 为 `session:last_activity`\n47: - [ ] 3.4 实现 `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)` — 空 sessionID 返回错误；零时间使用 `time.Now()`；`EXISTS` 验证 key 存在，不存在返回 `ErrNotFound`；`ZADD` 更新 activity score\n48: - [ ] 3.5 运行 `go build ./pkg/store/...` 确认编译通过\n49: \n50: **Verification:** 方法签名与 design.md §3.1 一致；List 方法使用逐个 GET 调用（非 MGET）；孤儿 ZSET 成员被跳过\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## T4. 编写 Valkey 单元测试\n55: \n56: - [ ] 4.1 创建 `store_valkey_test.go`\n57: - [ ] 4.2 编写 `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_NilInfo` — nil sandbox 输入返回 `\"sandbox is nil\"`\n58: - [ ] 4.3 编写 `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` — 零 ExpiresAt 返回 `\"ExpiresAt is zero\"`\n59: - [ ] 4.4 编写 `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_NilInfo` — nil sandbox 输入返回 `\"sandbox is nil\"`\n60: - [ ] 4.5 编写 `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_EmptySessionID` — 空 sessionID 返回 `\"sessionID is empty\"`\n61: - [ ] 4.6 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_LimitZero` — limit=0 返回 `nil, nil`\n62: - [ ] 4.7 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_LimitNegative` — limit=-5 返回 `nil, nil`\n63: - [ ] 4.8 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_LimitZero` — limit=0 返回 `nil, nil`\n64: - [ ] 4.9 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_LimitNegative` — limit=-1 返回 `nil, nil`\n65: - [ ] 4.10 编写 `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime` — 零时间使用 `time.Now()` 替代\n66: - [ ] 4.11 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_ScoreCalculation` — 1 小时前 score = -3600\n67: - [ ] 4.12 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_ScoreCalculation` — 2 小时前 score = -7200\n68: - [ ] 4.13 编写 `TestValkeyStore_StructFields` — 常量值断言\n69: - [ ] 4.14 编写 `TestValkeyStore_InterfaceCompliance` — 编译期 `var _ Store = (*valkeyStore)(nil)`\n70: - [ ] 4.15 运行 `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -count=1` 全部通过\n71: \n72: **Verification:** 测试覆盖 design.md §5.1 测试矩阵全部用例；`go test -cover ./pkg/store/...` 覆盖率 ≥ 80%\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## T5. 竞态检测与门禁验证\n77: \n78: - [ ] 5.1 运行 `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` 无 data race 警告\n79: - [ ] 5.2 确认无 `log.Printf` 使用（仅允许 `klog`）\n80: - [ ] 5.3 确认日志中无敏感数据（密码、连接字符串）\n81: - [ ] 5.4 运行 `go vet ./pkg/store/...` 无警告\n82: - [ ] 5.5 运行 `go mod tidy` 确保依赖正确\n83: - [ ] 5.6 确认 `go build ./pkg/store/...` 编译通过\n84: \n85: **Verification:** 以上 6 项全部通过\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## Task Dependencies\n90: \n91: ```\n92: T1 ──→ T2 ──→ T3 ──→ T4 ──→ T5\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ## Acceptance Criteria\n96: \n97: | # | Criterion | Command |\n98: |---|-----------|---------|\n99: | AC1 | 编译通过 | `go build ./pkg/store/...` |\n100: | AC2 | 全部测试通过 | `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -count=1` |\n101: | AC3 | 无竞态条件 | `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` |\n102: | AC4 | 覆盖率 ≥ 80% | `go test -cover ./pkg/store/...` |\n103: | AC5 | 无 lint 警告 | `go vet ./pkg/store/...` |\n104: | AC6 | Store 接口 10 个方法全部实现 | `var _ Store = (*valkeyStore)(nil)` 编译通过 |\n105: | AC7 | List 方法使用逐个 GET 调用（非 MGET） | 代码审查 |\n106: | AC8 | `StoreSandbox` 拒绝零 ExpiresAt | `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` 通过 |\n107: | AC9 | 构造函数返回 error 而非 klog.Fatal | 代码审查 + 单元测试 |\n108: | AC10 | `STORE_TYPE=valkey` 时 singleton 选择 Valkey 后端 | 代码审查 |\n109: | AC11 | 孤儿 ZSET 成员在 List 方法中被跳过 | 代码审查 |\n\n(End of file - total 109 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** pkg/store\n> **Language:** Go\n> **Size:** S\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-014/design.md`, `changes/AR-014/proposal.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n\n## T1. 实现 Valkey 构造函数\n\n- [ ] 1.1 创建 `store_valkey.go`，定义 `valkeyStore` 结构体（`cli valkey.Client`, `sessionPrefix`, `expiryIndexKey`, `lastActivityIndexKey`）\n- [ ] 1.2 实现 `newValkeyStore() (Store, error)` 构造函数\n- [ ] 1.3 验证 `VALKEY_ADDR` 非空，否则返回 `errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")`\n- [ ] 1.4 验证 `VALKEY_PASSWORD`（除非 `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`）\n- [ ] 1.5 支持 `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` 和 `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` 环境变量\n- [ ] 1.6 使用 `valkey.NewClient` 创建客户端（不执行 ping，连接惰性验证）\n- [ ] 1.7 更新 `singleton.go` 中 `initStore()` 支持 `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n- [ ] 1.8 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingAddr`\n- [ ] 1.9 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingPassword`\n- [ ] 1.10 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordNotRequired`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775837184170,"end":1775837184177}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775837187098,"sessionID":"ses_287ddf2ddffeKgyYIqXjT8EJwx","part":{"id":"prt_d782501b1001ipeUbJTcwKoDVq","messageID":"msg_d7824f0620017jWk1nS11Z7NyU","sessionID":"ses_287ddf2ddffeKgyYIqXjT8EJwx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_836b4a494eb041769fc50987","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `pkg/store`\n6: - **Language:** Go\n7: - **Size:** S\n8: - **Base specs:** `session-store/spec.md`, `session-store/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: Valkey client initialization\n13: The Valkey implementation SHALL construct a `valkey.Client` using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`. The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` to be non-empty (comma-separated list split into `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`.\n14: \n15: #### Scenario: Successful initialization with address and password\n16: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set to `\"localhost:6379\"` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is set to `\"secret\"`\n17: - **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n18: - **THEN** a `valkey.Client` is constructed with `InitAddress: []string{\"localhost:6379\"}` and `Password: \"secret\"`\n19: - **AND** no error is returned\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Comma-separated addresses\n22: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set to `\"host1:6379,host2:6379\"`\n23: - **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n24: - **THEN** `InitAddress` is `[]string{\"host1:6379\", \"host2:6379\"}`\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Missing address fails\n27: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is empty or unset\n28: - **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n29: - **THEN** initialization returns an error indicating `VALKEY_ADDR` is required\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n32: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set, `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty, and `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n33: - **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n34: - **THEN** initialization fails with an error stating password is required\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Password bypass when explicitly disabled\n37: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set, `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty, and `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set to `\"false\"` (case-insensitive)\n38: - **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n39: - **THEN** a `valkey.Client` is constructed with empty password\n40: - **AND** no error is returned\n41: \n42: ### Requirement: Valkey connection options\n43: The system SHALL build `valkey.ClientOption` with `InitAddress` from splitting `VALKEY_ADDR` by comma and `Password` from `VALKEY_PASSWORD`. Optional flags `DisableCache` and `ForceSingleClient` SHALL be set when their respective environment variables parse as true via `strconv.ParseBool`.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Options construction with defaults\n46: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=\"valkey-host:6380\"` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD=\"pass123\"`\n47: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n48: - **THEN** the returned `ClientOption` has `InitAddress: []string{\"valkey-host:6380\"}` and `Password: \"pass123\"`\n49: - **AND** `DisableCache` and `ForceSingleClient` are `false`\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: DisableCache enabled\n52: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n53: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n54: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is `true` on `ClientOption`\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: ForceSingleClient enabled\n57: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n58: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n59: - **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is `true` on `ClientOption`\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Invalid bool value ignored\n62: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=invalid`\n63: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n64: - **THEN** `DisableCache` remains `false` (ParseBool error, flag not set)\n65: \n66: ### Requirement: Valkey StoreSandbox multi-command execution\n67: The Valkey implementation SHALL execute `StoreSandbox` via `DoMulti` with three commands: `SETNX` on the session key with JSON value, `ZADD` on `session:expiry` with score = `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())`, and `ZADD` on `session:last_activity` with score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())`. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch returns an error.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Successful store multi\n70: - **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with non-zero `ExpiresAt` and session id `s1`\n71: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called on the Valkey store\n72: - **THEN** `DoMulti` executes `SETNX session:s1 <json>`, `ZADD session:expiry <expires_unix> s1`, `ZADD session:last_activity <now_unix> s1` and returns nil\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: Multi error propagation\n75: - **GIVEN** the Valkey server is unreachable during `StoreSandbox`\n76: - **WHEN** `DoMulti` executes\n77: - **THEN** the method returns a non-nil error and no partial state is committed\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n80: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n81: - **WHEN** the method executes\n82: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating sandbox is nil\n83: - **AND** no Valkey commands are issued\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n86: - **GIVEN** `SandboxInfo` has `ExpiresAt == time.Time{}`\n87: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n88: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating ExpiresAt is required\n89: - **AND** no Valkey commands are issued\n90: \n91: ### Requirement: Valkey UpdateSandbox XX semantics\n92: The Valkey implementation SHALL use `SET key value XX` for `UpdateSandbox`. If the key does not exist, the response will not be `\"OK\"` and the system SHALL return an error indicating the key does not exist.\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Update existing key\n95: - **GIVEN** session key `session:s1` exists\n96: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n97: - **THEN** the JSON value is overwritten, response is `\"OK\"`, and the method returns nil\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Update missing key\n100: - **GIVEN** session key `session:s1` does not exist\n101: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n102: - **THEN** the method returns an error containing `key not exists`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected on update\n105: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n106: - **WHEN** the method executes\n107: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating sandbox is nil\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID multi-command execution\n110: The Valkey implementation SHALL execute `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` via `DoMulti` with three commands: `DEL` on the session key, `ZREM` on `session:expiry`, and `ZREM` on `session:last_activity`.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Full deletion\n113: - **GIVEN** session `s1` exists with entries in both ZSETs\n114: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\")` succeeds\n115: - **THEN** `GET session:s1` returns not found and both ZSETs no longer contain member `s1`\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Delete non-existent session\n118: - **GIVEN** session `ghost` does not exist\n119: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"ghost\")` is called\n120: - **THEN** `DoMulti` executes (DEL returns 0, ZREM returns 0) and no error is returned\n121: \n122: ### Requirement: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID\n123: The Valkey implementation SHALL retrieve a sandbox document using `B().Get().Key(key)`. If the key does not exist (`IsValkeyNil` returns true), the system SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Existing session retrieved\n126: - **GIVEN** a sandbox document exists at key `session:s1`\n127: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\")` is called\n128: - **THEN** the bytes are unmarshaled to `*types.SandboxInfo` and returned with nil error\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Missing session returns ErrNotFound\n131: - **GIVEN** no key exists at `session:missing`\n132: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"missing\")` is called\n133: - **THEN** `IsValkeyNil` is true and the method returns `ErrNotFound`\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes query\n136: The Valkey implementation SHALL query `session:expiry` using `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, and `Limit(0, limit)`. When `limit <= 0`, the method SHALL return `nil, nil`.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: List with limit zero\n139: - **GIVEN** expired sessions exist in the index\n140: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` is called\n141: - **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: List with positive limit\n144: - **GIVEN** three sessions have expiry scores ≤ `before.Unix()`\n145: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 2)` is called\n146: - **THEN** at most two `SandboxInfo` pointers are returned\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: List with negative limit\n149: - **GIVEN** expired sessions exist\n150: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, -1)` is called\n151: - **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil`\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes query\n154: The Valkey implementation SHALL query `session:last_activity` using `Zrangebyscore` with the same score range pattern as `ListExpiredSandboxes`. When `limit <= 0`, the method SHALL return `nil, nil`.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Inactive list with negative limit\n157: - **GIVEN** inactive sessions exist\n158: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, -1)` is called\n159: - **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Inactive list with positive limit\n162: - **GIVEN** two sessions have last-activity scores ≤ `before.Unix()`\n163: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, 5)` is called\n164: - **THEN** up to two `SandboxInfo` pointers are returned\n165: \n166: ### Requirement: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity precondition\n167: The Valkey implementation SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists via `B().Exists().Key(key)` (result must be 1). If the key is absent, the method SHALL return `ErrNotFound`. Then `ZADD` the session id to `session:last_activity` with the activity score.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Activity update with zero time\n170: - **GIVEN** session `s1` exists and `at` is `time.Time{}`\n171: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at)` is called\n172: - **THEN** `ZADD session:last_activity <now_unix> s1` is executed\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Activity update for missing session\n175: - **GIVEN** session `s1` does not exist\n176: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", now)` is called\n177: - **THEN** `Exists` returns 0 and the method returns `ErrNotFound`\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Empty session ID rejected\n180: - **GIVEN** empty session ID `\"\"`\n181: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at)` is called\n182: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating session ID is empty\n183: \n184: ### Requirement: Valkey MGET orphan tolerance\n185: The Valkey implementation SHALL handle empty string results from `Mget` commands when loading sandboxes by session IDs via `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs`. Entries with empty string results SHALL be skipped without failing the batch.\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Valkey orphan ZSET member\n188: - **GIVEN** session id `ghost` is in `session:last_activity` but `session:ghost` does not exist\n189: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` loads the batch via `Mget`\n190: - **THEN** `ghost` is omitted from the result slice\n191: - **AND** no error is raised\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: All keys present in MGET\n194: - **GIVEN** session ids `[\"a\", \"b\"]` both have corresponding keys with valid JSON\n195: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, [\"a\", \"b\"])` is called\n196: - **THEN** `Mget` returns both values and both are unmarshaled into the result slice\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Mixed present and missing keys\n199: - **GIVEN** session id `a` has a key but `b` does not\n200: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, [\"a\", \"b\"])` is called\n201: - **THEN** `b`'s empty result is skipped and only `a`'s `SandboxInfo` is returned\n202: \n203: ### Requirement: Valkey Ping response validation\n204: The Valkey implementation SHALL issue `PING` via `B().Ping()` and validate the string response equals `PONG`.\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Healthy Valkey\n207: - **GIVEN** Valkey server is running\n208: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n209: - **THEN** the response is `PONG` and nil error is returned\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Unreachable Valkey\n212: - **GIVEN** Valkey server is down\n213: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n214: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating connection failure\n215: \n216: ### Requirement: Valkey Close operation\n217: The Valkey implementation SHALL close the client connection via `vs.cli.Close()` and return nil.\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Client closed successfully\n220: - **GIVEN** an active Valkey store\n221: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n222: - **THEN** `vs.cli.Close()` is invoked and nil is returned\n223: \n224: ### Requirement: Valkey fixed key patterns\n225: The Valkey implementation SHALL use the following fixed key patterns: `sessionPrefix = \"session:\"`, `expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"`, `lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"`.\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Session key construction\n228: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n229: - **WHEN** the store constructs the key\n230: - **THEN** the key is `session:abc`\n231: \n232: ### Requirement: Valkey ZSET score semantics\n233: The system SHALL use Unix seconds as scores in sorted sets. Expiry index score = `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store. Last activity score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`, `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: Expiry score is sandbox ExpiresAt\n236: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` set to a specific time T\n237: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` adds to `session:expiry`\n238: - **THEN** the score is `float64(T.Unix())`\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: Last activity score is current time on store\n241: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox` is called at time T\n242: - **WHEN** the sandbox is added to `session:last_activity`\n243: - **THEN** the score is `float64(T.Unix())`\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Last activity score uses provided time on update\n246: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with time T\n247: - **WHEN** the ZADD is executed on `session:last_activity`\n248: - **THEN** the score is `float64(T.Unix())`\n249: \n250: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE for Valkey\n251: When `STORE_TYPE` is set case-insensitively to `\"valkey\"`, the system SHALL construct the Valkey implementation.\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Valkey selected\n254: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"valkey\"`\n255: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n256: - **THEN** the Valkey implementation is constructed\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Case-insensitive valkey match\n259: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"VALKEY\"`\n260: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n261: - **THEN** the Valkey implementation is constructed\n262: \n263: ### Requirement: Valkey struct definition\n264: The Valkey implementation SHALL define a `valkeyStore` struct with fields: `cli valkey.Client`, `sessionPrefix string`, `expiryIndexKey string`, `lastActivityIndexKey string`.\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: Struct field initialization\n267: - **GIVEN** a new `valkeyStore` is constructed\n268: - **WHEN** fields are inspected\n269: - **THEN** `sessionPrefix` is `\"session:\"`, `expiryIndexKey` is `\"session:expiry\"`, `lastActivityIndexKey` is `\"session:last_activity\"`\n\n(End of file - total 269 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `pkg/store`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** S\n- **Base specs:** `session-store/spec.md`, `session-store/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Valkey client initialization\nThe Valkey implementation SHALL construct a `valkey.Client` using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`. The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` to be non-empty (comma-separated list split into `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful initialization with address and password\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set to `\"localhost:6379\"` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is set to `\"secret\"`\n- **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n- **THEN** a `valkey.Client` is constructed with `InitAddress: []string{\"localhost:6379\"}` and `Password: \"secret\"`\n- **AND** no error is returned\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775837187091,"end":1775837187097}}}}
